reviewText: Nice set of DVD's on Muscle cars.  It interviews the owners of classic muscle cars.  Nice to get a close up look and to hear the engines running!  If you are into muscle cars or know someone who is it would make a great gift.  Look for a reasonable price.  I have seen some high asking prices and I don't think it is worth paying a premium for.

To much Dennis Gage.  I personally don't dislike the guy, but I was hoping for more car history with nostalgic detail information, ads, history, and film clips (past and present) of the cars instead of Dennis riding in them.  Leno on the other hand is a treat to see and listen to because of his indepth knowledge of the cars/rides/machinery he owns.  I could enjoy watching a single DVD of Leno by himself describing his vast collection of automobiles, bikes, and machinery.  On the upside; the DVD's do present some great spots on some beautiful and interesting cars.
My husband is a huge car buff. This video has a little bit of everything for the classic car enthusiast.

I bought this set as a Christmas gift for a friend.  After watching it, he told me how much he loved everything about them.  Being a fancier of older cars, he said the gift was very nostalgic for him.
This is a perfect video/gift for someone who LOVES muscle cars! It's entertaining and fun to watch. So glad I purchased it.
My husband and my father in law spent most of Christmas afternoon watching these together.  Good bonding experience for them.
The DVD arrived promptly And was exactly as it was presented.  I have enjoyed the various shows of this collection.
With this dvd set, I have retained my title of "cool aunt" in the eyes of my 20 year old gear head nephew! He loved it!

This set was purchased for a friend who enjoys muscle cars and car auctions.  He has seen specials on Jay Leno's collection but this was much more detailed.  It was a great gift for a reasonable price.
